cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the task of identifying potential abuses of human rights through imagery using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves transfer learning and fine-tuning of CNNs, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve evaluating the performance of different CNN features, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the sensitive topic of human rights violations, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
